casadi::FmuFunction Class Reference

#include <fmu_function.hpp>

Detailed Description


List of available options
IdTypeDescriptionUsed in
abstolOT_DOUBLEAbsolute error tolerance, scaled by nominal valuecasadi::FmuFunction
ad_weightOT_DOUBLEWeighting factor for derivative calculation.When there is an option of either using forward or reverse mode directional derivatives, the condition ad_weight*nf<=(1-ad_weight)*na is used where nf and na are estimates of the number of forward/reverse mode directional derivatives needed. By default, ad_weight is calculated automatically, but this can be overridden by setting this option. In particular, 0 means forcing forward mode and 1 forcing reverse mode. Leave unset for (class specific) heuristics.casadi::FunctionInternal
ad_weight_spOT_DOUBLEWeighting factor for sparsity pattern calculation calculation.Overrides default behavior. Set to 0 and 1 to force forward and reverse mode respectively. Cf. option "ad_weight". When set to -1, sparsity is completely ignored and dense matrices are used.casadi::FunctionInternal
always_inlineOT_BOOLForce inlining.casadi::FunctionInternal

enable_jacobianOT_BOOLEnable derivative calculation using generated functions for Jacobians of all differentiable outputs with respect to all differentiable inputs - if available. [default: true]casadi::FunctionInternal
enable_reverseOT_BOOLEnable derivative calculation using generated functions for transposed Jacobian-times-vector products - typically using reverse mode AD - if available. [default: true]casadi::FunctionInternal

is_diff_outOT_BOOLVECTORIndicate for each output if it should be differentiable.casadi::FunctionInternal
jac_penaltyOT_DOUBLEWhen requested for a number of forward/reverse directions, it may be cheaper to compute first the full jacobian and then multiply with seeds, rather than obtain the requested directions in a straightforward manner. Casadi uses a heuristic to decide which is cheaper. A high value of 'jac_penalty' makes it less likely for the heurstic to chose the full Jacobian strategy. The special value -1 indicates never to use the full Jacobian strategycasadi::FunctionInternal

2912  std::vector<MX>::const_iterator J_it = J.begin();
2913  for (size_t oind = 0; oind < n_out_; ++oind) {
2914  for (size_t iind = 0; iind < n_in_; ++iind) {
2915  // Add contribution
2916  MX a = mtimes(*J_it++, all_fseed[iind]);
2917  all_fsens[oind] = all_fsens[oind].is_empty(true) ? a : all_fsens[oind] + a;
2918  }
2919  }
2920  // Split forward sensitivities
2921  for (size_t d = 0; d < nfwd; ++d) fsens[d].resize(n_out_);
2922  for (size_t i = 0; i < n_out_; ++i) {
2923  v = horzsplit(all_fsens[i]);
2924  casadi_assert_dev(v.size() == nfwd);
2925  for (size_t d = 0; d < nfwd; ++d) fsens[d][i] = reshape(v[d], size_out(i));
2926  }
2927  } else {
2928  // Evaluate in batches
2929  casadi_assert_dev(enable_forward_ || enable_fd_);
2930  casadi_int max_nfwd = max_num_dir_;
2931  if (!enable_fd_) {
2932  while (!has_forward(max_nfwd)) max_nfwd/=2;
2933  }
2934  casadi_int offset = 0;
2935  while (offset<nfwd) {
2936  // Number of derivatives, in this batch
2937  casadi_int nfwd_batch = std::min(nfwd-offset, max_nfwd);
2938 
2939  // All inputs and seeds
2940  std::vector<MX> darg;
2941  darg.reserve(n_in_ + n_out_ + n_in_);
2942  darg.insert(darg.end(), arg.begin(), arg.end());
2943  darg.insert(darg.end(), res.begin(), res.end());
2944  std::vector<MX> v(nfwd_batch);
2945  for (casadi_int i=0; i<n_in_; ++i) {
2946  for (casadi_int d=0; d<nfwd_batch; ++d) v[d] = fseed[offset+d][i];
2947  darg.push_back(horzcat(v));
2948  }
2949 
2950  // Create the evaluation node
2951  Function dfcn = self().forward(nfwd_batch);
2952  std::vector<MX> x = dfcn(darg);
2953 
2954  casadi_assert_dev(x.size()==n_out_);
2955 
2956  // Retrieve sensitivities
2957  for (casadi_int d=0; d<nfwd_batch; ++d) fsens[offset+d].resize(n_out_);
2958  for (casadi_int i=0; i<n_out_; ++i) {
2959  if (size2_out(i)>0) {
2960  v = horzsplit(x[i], size2_out(i));
2961  casadi_assert_dev(v.size()==nfwd_batch);
2962  } else {
2963  v = std::vector<MX>(nfwd_batch, MX(size_out(i)));
2964  }
2965  for (casadi_int d=0; d<nfwd_batch; ++d) fsens[offset+d][i] = v[d];
2966  }
2967 
2968  // Update offset
2969  offset += nfwd_batch;
2970  }
2971  }
2972  }

2018  for (const std::string& n : name_io) {
2019  // Find end of prefix, skip if no prefix
2020  size_t end = n.find('_');
2021  if (end >= n.size()) continue;
2022  // Skip if too short
2023  if (end < prefix.size()) continue;
2024  // Skip if wrong prefix
2025  if (n.compare(0, prefix.size(), prefix) != 0) continue;
2026  // Beginning of index
2027  size_t begin = prefix.size();
2028  // Check if any index
2029  casadi_int this_index;
2030  if (begin == end) {
2031  // No prefix, implicitly 1
2032  this_index = 1;
2033  } else {
2034  // Read index from string
2035  this_index = std::stoi(n.substr(begin, end - begin));
2036  }
2037  // Find the highest index
2038  if (this_index > highest_index) highest_index = this_index;
2039  }
2040  }
2041  // Return one higher index
2042  if (highest_index == 0) {
2043  return prefix + "_";
2044  } else {
2045  return prefix + std::to_string(highest_index + 1) + "_";
2046  }
2047  }

1945  casadi_int mode_fwd = test_fwd_first ? 0 : 1;
1946 
1947  // Test both coloring modes
1948  for (casadi_int mode=0; mode<2; ++mode) {
1949  // Is this the forward mode?
1950  bool fwd = mode==mode_fwd;
1951 
1952  // Skip?
1953  if (!allow_forward && fwd) continue;
1954  if (!allow_reverse && !fwd) continue;
1955 
1956  // Perform the coloring
1957  if (fwd) {
1958  if (verbose_) casadi_message("Unidirectional coloring (forward mode)");
1959  bool d = best_coloring>=w*static_cast<double>(A.size1());
1960  casadi_int max_colorings_to_test =
1961  d ? A.size1() : static_cast<casadi_int>(floor(best_coloring/w));
1962  D1 = AT.uni_coloring(A, max_colorings_to_test);
1963  if (D1.is_null()) {
1964  if (verbose_) {
1965  casadi_message("Forward mode coloring interrupted (more than "
1966  + str(max_colorings_to_test) + " needed).");
1967  }
1968  } else {
1969  if (verbose_) {
1970  casadi_message("Forward mode coloring completed: "
1971  + str(D1.size2()) + " directional derivatives needed ("
1972  + str(A.size1()) + " without coloring).");
1973  }
1974  D2 = Sparsity();
1975  best_coloring = w*static_cast<double>(D1.size2());
1976  }
1977  } else {
1978  if (verbose_) casadi_message("Unidirectional coloring (adjoint mode)");
1979  bool d = best_coloring>=(1-w)*static_cast<double>(A.size2());
1980  casadi_int max_colorings_to_test =
1981  d ? A.size2() : static_cast<casadi_int>(floor(best_coloring/(1-w)));
1982 
1983  D2 = A.uni_coloring(AT, max_colorings_to_test);
1984  if (D2.is_null()) {
1985  if (verbose_) {
1986  casadi_message("Adjoint mode coloring interrupted (more than "
1987  + str(max_colorings_to_test) + " needed).");
1988  }
1989  } else {
1990  if (verbose_) {
1991  casadi_message("Adjoint mode coloring completed: "
1992  + str(D2.size2()) + " directional derivatives needed ("
1993  + str(A.size2()) + " without coloring).");
1994  }
1995  D1 = Sparsity();
1996  best_coloring = (1-w)*static_cast<double>(D2.size2());
1997  }
1998  }
1999  }
2000 
2001  }

316  + " not enabled during compilation. Falling back to serial evaluation");
317  parallelization_ = Parallelization::SERIAL;
318  break;
319  }
320 
321  // Collect all inputs in any Jacobian, Hessian or adjoint block
322  std::vector<size_t> in_jac(fmu_.n_in(), 0);
323  jac_in_.clear();
324  jac_nom_in_.clear();
325  for (auto&& i : out_) {
326  if (i.type == OutputType::JAC || i.type == OutputType::JAC_TRANS
327  || i.type == OutputType::ADJ || i.type == OutputType::HESS) {
328  // Get input indices
329  const std::vector<size_t>& iind = fmu_.ired(i.wrt);
330  // Skip if no entries
331  if (iind.empty()) continue;
332  // Consistency check
333  bool exists = in_jac[iind.front()] > 0;
334  for (size_t j : iind) casadi_assert((in_jac[j] > 0) == exists, "Jacobian not a block");
335  // Add selection
336  if (!exists) {
337  for (size_t j : iind) {
338  jac_in_.push_back(j);
339  jac_nom_in_.push_back(fmu_.nominal_in(j));
340  in_jac[j] = jac_in_.size();
341  }
342  }
343  // Add column interval
344  i.cbegin = in_jac[iind.front()] - 1;
345  i.cend = i.cbegin + iind.size();
346  // Also rows for Hessian blocks
347  if (i.type == OutputType::HESS) {
348  // Get input indices
349  const std::vector<size_t>& iind = fmu_.ired(i.ind);
350  // Skip if no entries
351  if (iind.empty()) continue;
352  // Consistency check
353  bool exists = in_jac[iind.front()] > 0;
354  for (size_t j : iind) casadi_assert((in_jac[j] > 0) == exists, "Hessian not a block");
355  // Add selection
356  if (!exists) {
357  for (size_t j : iind) {
358  jac_in_.push_back(j);
359  jac_nom_in_.push_back(fmu_.nominal_in(j));
360  in_jac[j] = jac_in_.size();
361  }
362  }
363  // Add column interval
364  i.rbegin = in_jac[iind.front()] - 1;
365  i.rend = i.rbegin + iind.size();
366  }
367  }
368  }
369 
370  // Transpose of Jacobian sparsity
371  sp_trans_map_.resize(out_.size(), -1);
372  sp_trans_.clear();
373 
374  // Collect all outputs in any Jacobian or adjoint block
375  in_jac.resize(fmu_.n_out());
376  std::fill(in_jac.begin(), in_jac.end(), 0);
377  jac_out_.clear();
378  for (size_t k = 0; k < out_.size(); ++k) {
379  OutputStruct& i = out_[k];
380  if (i.type == OutputType::JAC || i.type == OutputType::JAC_TRANS) {
381  // Get output indices
382  const std::vector<size_t>& oind = fmu_.ored(i.ind);
383  // Skip if no entries
384  if (oind.empty()) continue;
385  // Consistency check
386  bool exists = in_jac[oind.front()] > 0;
387  for (size_t j : oind) casadi_assert((in_jac[j] > 0) == exists, "Jacobian not a block");
388  // Add selection
389  if (!exists) {
390  for (size_t j : oind) {
391  jac_out_.push_back(j);
392  in_jac[j] = jac_out_.size();
393  }
394  }
395  // Add row interval
396  i.rbegin = in_jac[oind.front()] - 1;
397  i.rend = i.rbegin + oind.size();
398  // Additional memory for transpose
399  if (i.type == OutputType::JAC_TRANS) {
400  // Retrieve the sparsity pattern
401  const Sparsity& sp = sparsity_out(k);
402  // Save transpose of sparsity pattern
403  sp_trans_map_.at(k) = sp_trans_.size();
404  sp_trans_.push_back(sp.T());
405  // Work vectors for casadi_trans
406  alloc_w(sp.nnz());
407  alloc_iw(sp.size2());
408  }
409  }
410  }
411  for (auto&& i : in_) {
412  if (i.type == InputType::ADJ) {
413  // Get output indices
414  const std::vector<size_t>& oind = fmu_.ored(i.ind);
415  // Skip if no entries
416  if (oind.empty()) continue;
417  // Consistency check
418  bool exists = in_jac[oind.front()] > 0;
419  for (size_t j : oind) casadi_assert((in_jac[j] > 0) == exists, "Jacobian not a block");
420  // Add selection
421  if (!exists) {
422  for (size_t j : oind) {
423  jac_out_.push_back(j);
424  in_jac[j] = jac_out_.size();
425  }
426  }
427  }
428  }
429 
430  // Get sparsity pattern for extended Jacobian
431  jac_sp_ = fmu_.jac_sparsity(jac_out_, jac_in_);
432 
433  // Calculate graph coloring
434  jac_colors_ = jac_sp_.uni_coloring();
435  if (verbose_) casadi_message("Jacobian graph coloring: " + str(jac_sp_.size2())
436  + " -> " + str(jac_colors_.size2()) + " directions");
437 
438  // Setup Jacobian memory
439  casadi_jac_setup(&p_, jac_sp_, jac_colors_);
440  p_.nom_in = get_ptr(jac_nom_in_);
441  p_.map_out = get_ptr(jac_out_);
442  p_.map_in = get_ptr(jac_in_);
443 
444  // Do not use more threads than there are colors in the Jacobian
445  max_jac_tasks_ = std::min(max_n_tasks_, jac_colors_.size2());
446 
447  // Work vector for storing extended Jacobian, shared between threads
448  if (has_jac_) {
449  alloc_w(jac_sp_.nnz(), true); // jac_nz
450  }
451 
452  // Work vectors for adjoint derivative calculation, shared between threads
453  if (has_adj_) {
454  alloc_w(fmu_.n_out(), true); // aseed
455  alloc_w(fmu_.n_in(), true); // asens
456  }
457 
458  // If Hessian calculation is needed
459  if (has_hess_) {
460  // Get sparsity pattern for extended Hessian
461  hess_sp_ = fmu_.hess_sparsity(jac_in_, jac_in_);
462  casadi_assert(hess_sp_.size1() == jac_in_.size(), "Inconsistent Hessian dimensions");
463  casadi_assert(hess_sp_.size2() == jac_in_.size(), "Inconsistent Hessian dimensions");
464  const casadi_int *hess_row = hess_sp_.row();
465  casadi_int hess_nnz = hess_sp_.nnz();
466 
467  // Get nonlinearly entering variables
468  std::vector<bool> is_nonlin(jac_in_.size(), false);
469  for (casadi_int k = 0; k < hess_nnz; ++k) is_nonlin[hess_row[k]] = true;
470  nonlin_.clear();
471  for (casadi_int c = 0; c < jac_in_.size(); ++c) {
472  if (is_nonlin[c]) nonlin_.push_back(c);
473  }
474  // Calculate graph coloring
475  if (hessian_coloring_) {
476  // Star coloring
477  hess_colors_ = hess_sp_.star_coloring();
478  if (verbose_) casadi_message("Hessian graph coloring: " + str(nonlin_.size())
479  + " -> " + str(hess_colors_.size2()) + " directions");
480  // Indices of non-nonlinearly entering variables
481  std::vector<casadi_int> zind;
482  for (casadi_int c = 0; c < jac_in_.size(); ++c) {
483  if (!is_nonlin[c]) zind.push_back(c);
484  }
485  // Zero out corresponding rows
486  hess_colors_.erase(zind, range(hess_colors_.size2()));
487  } else {
488  // One color for each nonlinear variable
489  hess_colors_ = Sparsity(jac_in_.size(), nonlin_.size(), range(nonlin_.size() + 1), nonlin_);
490  if (verbose_) casadi_message("Hessian calculation for " + str(nonlin_.size()) + " variables");
491  }
492 
493  // Number of threads to be used for Hessian calculation
494  max_hess_tasks_ = std::min(max_n_tasks_, hess_colors_.size2());
495 
496  // Work vector for storing extended Hessian, shared between threads
497  alloc_w(hess_sp_.nnz(), true); // hess_nz
498 
499  // Work vector for perturbed adjoint sensitivities
500  alloc_w(max_hess_tasks_ * fmu_.n_in(), true); // pert_asens
501 
502  // Work vector for avoiding conflicting assignments for star coloring
503  alloc_iw(max_hess_tasks_ * fmu_.n_in(), true); // star_iw
504 
505  // Work vector for making symmetric or checking symmetry
506  alloc_iw(hess_sp_.size2());
507  }
508 
509  // Total number of threads used for Jacobian/adjoint calculation
510  // Note: Adjoint calculation also used for Hessian
511  max_n_tasks_ = std::min(max_n_tasks_, std::max(max_jac_tasks_, max_hess_tasks_));
512  if (verbose_) casadi_message("Jacobian calculation with " + str(max_n_tasks_) + " threads");
513 
514  // Work vectors for Jacobian/adjoint/Hessian calculation, for each thread
515  casadi_int jac_iw, jac_w;
516  casadi_jac_work(&p_, &jac_iw, &jac_w);
517  alloc_iw(max_n_tasks_ * jac_iw, true);
518  alloc_w(max_n_tasks_ * jac_w, true);
519 }

3726  char buf[256];
3727  size_t buf_sz = sizeof(buf);
3728  char* buf_dyn = nullptr;

3730  casadi_int n = vsnprintf(buf, buf_sz, fmt, args);
3731  // Need a larger buffer?
3732  if (n>static_cast<casadi_int>(buf_sz)) {
3733  buf_sz = static_cast<size_t>(n+1);
3734  buf_dyn = new char[buf_sz];
3735  n = vsnprintf(buf_dyn, buf_sz, fmt, args);
3736  }
3737  // Print buffer content
3738  if (n>=0) uout() << (buf_dyn ? buf_dyn : buf) << std::flush;
3739  // Cleanup
3740  delete[] buf_dyn;
3741  va_end(args);
3742  // Throw error if failure
3743  casadi_assert(n>=0, "Print failure while processing '" + std::string(fmt) + "'");
